[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 9036,
        "end_time": 14106,
        "text": "You&#39;d have a hard time finding\nK\u00f6nigsberg on any modern maps,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 14106,
        "end_time": 17415,
        "text": "but one particular quirk in its geography"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 17415,
        "end_time": 22205,
        "text": "has made it one of the most famous cities\nin mathematics."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 22205,
        "end_time": 26214,
        "text": "The medieval German city lay on both sides\nof the Pregel River."
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 26214,
        "end_time": 28875,
        "text": "At the center were two large islands."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 28875,
        "end_time": 33124,
        "text": "The two islands were connected \nto each other and to the river banks"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 33124,
        "end_time": 35884,
        "text": "by seven bridges."
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 35884,
        "end_time": 41296,
        "text": "Carl Gottlieb Ehler, a mathematician who\nlater became the mayor of a nearby town,"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 41296,
        "end_time": 44395,
        "text": "grew obsessed with these islands\nand bridges."
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 44395,
        "end_time": 47205,
        "text": "He kept coming back to a single question:"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 47205,
        "end_time": 51095,
        "text": "Which route would allow someone\nto cross all seven bridges"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 51095,
        "end_time": 55136,
        "text": "without crossing any of them\nmore than once?"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 55136,
        "end_time": 56946,
        "text": "Think about it for a moment."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 56946,
        "end_time": 57936,
        "text": "7"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 57936,
        "end_time": 58947,
        "text": "6"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 58947,
        "end_time": 59916,
        "text": "5"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 59916,
        "end_time": 60847,
        "text": "4"
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 60847,
        "end_time": 61956,
        "text": "3"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 61956,
        "end_time": 62886,
        "text": "2"
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 62886,
        "end_time": 63996,
        "text": "1"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 63996,
        "end_time": 65076,
        "text": "Give up?"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 65076,
        "end_time": 66198,
        "text": "You should."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 66198,
        "end_time": 67513,
        "text": "It&#39;s not possible."
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 67513,
        "end_time": 72636,
        "text": "But attempting to explain why\nled famous mathematician Leonhard Euler"
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 72636,
        "end_time": 75997,
        "text": "to invent a new field of mathematics."
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 75997,
        "end_time": 78648,
        "text": "Carl wrote to Euler for help\nwith the problem."
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 78648,
        "end_time": 83367,
        "text": "Euler first dismissed the question as\nhaving nothing to do with math."
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 83367,
        "end_time": 85136,
        "text": "But the more he wrestled with it,"
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 85136,
        "end_time": 88977,
        "text": "the more it seemed there might\nbe something there after all."
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 88977,
        "end_time": 92906,
        "text": "The answer he came up with\nhad to do with a type of geometry"
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 92906,
        "end_time": 98258,
        "text": "that did not quite exist yet,\nwhat he called the Geometry of Position,"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 98258,
        "end_time": 101897,
        "text": "now known as Graph Theory."
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 101897,
        "end_time": 103443,
        "text": "Euler&#39;s first insight"
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 103443,
        "end_time": 108507,
        "text": "was that the route taken between entering\nan island or a riverbank and leaving it"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 108507,
        "end_time": 110578,
        "text": "didn&#39;t actually matter."
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 110578,
        "end_time": 114427,
        "text": "Thus, the map could be simplified with\neach of the four landmasses"
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 114427,
        "end_time": 116627,
        "text": "represented as a single point,"
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 116627,
        "end_time": 119297,
        "text": "what we now call a node,"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 119297,
        "end_time": 124198,
        "text": "with lines, or edges, between them\nto represent the bridges."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 124198,
        "end_time": 129619,
        "text": "And this simplified graph allows us\nto easily count the degrees of each node."
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 129619,
        "end_time": 133219,
        "text": "That&#39;s the number of bridges \neach land mass touches."
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 133219,
        "end_time": 134598,
        "text": "Why do the degrees matter?"
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 134598,
        "end_time": 136828,
        "text": "Well, according to the rules \nof the challenge,"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 136828,
        "end_time": 140678,
        "text": "once travelers arrive onto a landmass\nby one bridge,"
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 140678,
        "end_time": 143800,
        "text": "they would have to leave it \nvia a different bridge."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 143800,
        "end_time": 148168,
        "text": "In other words, the bridges leading\nto and from each node on any route"
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 148168,
        "end_time": 150587,
        "text": "must occur in distinct pairs,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 150587,
        "end_time": 154239,
        "text": "meaning that the number of bridges\ntouching each landmass visited"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 154239,
        "end_time": 156368,
        "text": "must be even."
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 156368,
        "end_time": 160029,
        "text": "The only possible exceptions would be\nthe locations of the beginning"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 160029,
        "end_time": 162267,
        "text": "and end of the walk."
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 162267,
        "end_time": 167218,
        "text": "Looking at the graph, it becomes apparent\nthat all four nodes have an odd degree."
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 167218,
        "end_time": 169187,
        "text": "So no matter which path is chosen,"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 169187,
        "end_time": 173440,
        "text": "at some point,\na bridge will have to be crossed twice."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 173440,
        "end_time": 177709,
        "text": "Euler used this proof to formulate\na general theory"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 177709,
        "end_time": 181721,
        "text": "that applies to all graphs with two\nor more nodes."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 181721,
        "end_time": 185790,
        "text": "A Eulerian path \nthat visits each edge only once"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 185790,
        "end_time": 189159,
        "text": "is only possible in one of two scenarios."
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 189159,
        "end_time": 193769,
        "text": "The first is when there are exactly\ntwo nodes of odd degree,"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 193769,
        "end_time": 196310,
        "text": "meaning all the rest are even."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 196310,
        "end_time": 199659,
        "text": "There, the starting point is one\nof the odd nodes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 199659,
        "end_time": 201770,
        "text": "and the end point is the other."
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 201770,
        "end_time": 206091,
        "text": "The second is when all the nodes\nare of even degree."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 206091,
        "end_time": 211231,
        "text": "Then, the Eulerian path will start\nand stop in the same location,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 211231,
        "end_time": 214758,
        "text": "which also makes it something called\na Eulerian circuit."
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 214758,
        "end_time": 218460,
        "text": "So how might you create a Eulerian path\nin K\u00f6nigsberg?"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 218460,
        "end_time": 219302,
        "text": "It&#39;s simple."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 219302,
        "end_time": 221402,
        "text": "Just remove any one bridge."
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 221402,
        "end_time": 226080,
        "text": "And it turns out, history created\na Eulerian path of its own."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 226080,
        "end_time": 230198,
        "text": "During World War II, the Soviet Air Force\ndestroyed two of the city&#39;s bridges,"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 230198,
        "end_time": 233531,
        "text": "making a Eulerian path easily possible."
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 233531,
        "end_time": 237291,
        "text": "Though, to be fair, that probably\nwasn&#39;t their intention."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 237291,
        "end_time": 240781,
        "text": "These bombings pretty much wiped\nK\u00f6nigsberg off the map,"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 240781,
        "end_time": 244910,
        "text": "and it was later rebuilt \nas the Russian city of Kaliningrad."
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 244910,
        "end_time": 249083,
        "text": "So while K\u00f6nigsberg and her seven bridges\nmay not be around anymore,"
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 249083,
        "end_time": 253361,
        "text": "they will be remembered throughout\nhistory by the seemingly trivial riddle"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 253361,
        "end_time": 257662,
        "text": "which led to the emergence of \na whole new field of mathematics."
    }
]